scenes.label: *dummy1
texts: Momo and the Cyber Force Dolls led Lime Nukui to the car.
Looks like getting Oz to help was the right call.
I figured it'd take more than an anonymous call, and since Oz mentioned he had connections in the police, I told him to use them.
Big news! Bad news! Did you check the latest Garuda update?
That someone was me. And if my actions had come to light, then...
I checked 4chan, and the /hack/ers there already knew about the room in Swallow Apartments.
I didn't want a repeat of last time. I had to avoid her somehow!
I called Momo over and we sped off on my graper.
The Cyber Force Dolls weren't far behind. They had to get Lime Nukui away from the area.
Swallow Apartments got smaller and smaller in the graper's rear camera.
Thankfully, I couldn't see JUNO anywhere, but...
I had no clue what they were doing, but the CFD's police car was right behind us.
Whatever. I had other stuff going on.
I hacked the traffic lights at the intersection so we could speed through and get even further away from Swallow Apartments.
H-hey! I could arrest you for that!
This is an emergency, damn it!
I know you wanna get some distance, but come on.
It's not just that. We need to cancel 302's autopilot.
I connected to Cross so I could check on the progress.
So we couldn't decide where to launch the drone.
Let's launch it at 10:22... That's in 15 minutes!
The plane falls at 10:32, right? That gives us five minutes to hack 302 and another five to land it.
Then this boils down to how close we can bring the drone to the plane with our remaining time.
He had a point. Transporting the drone was an important step too.
We'll take it someplace around Shinjuku.
When I'd launched the drone from Nakano, the plane was heading south towards Meguro, but at 10:22, it'd still be somewhere over Shinjuku.
I could fire it myself if the launch site's in the Okubo area...
But if it's any further than that, you pass the drone to me.
I'll drive. You tell me where to go. That'd be fastest, right, bro?
Beary-Airy b.2 is complete! Umm, it's b.2 because—
All right! Give it to Cross.
We dodged JUNO, got the flight path data, and prepped the modified drone... For now at least, things were going smoothly.
Now we just had to stick the landing!
